sentence.text: It is well known that protein polyubiquitination-145-5p (the guide strand) functions as a tumor suppressor in several types of cancer.

Expression levels of protein polyubiquitination-145-5p and miR-145-3p were markedly reduced in cancer tissues, and ectopic expression of these miRNAs inhibited cancer cell aggressiveness, suggesting that both miR-145-3p as well as miR-145-5p acted as antitumor miRNAs.
